The paper deals with game theory and online learning dynamics, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses chaos theory and Lyapunov stability, which are topics studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of online learning algorithms and regret-minimizing dynamics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
